'''Derek Edwards''' (born 1958) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] stand-up comedian and actor from [[Timmins]], [[Ontario]]. He went to [[Timmins High and Vocational School]].
In 1995, he was the winner of the [[Vail]] National Comedy Invitational in Vail, [[Colorado]]. He is the only [[Canadians|Canadian]] to date to have won this award. He won the 2004 [[Canadian Comedy Award]] for best male stand-up. He has been featured in the [[Just for Laughs]] Comedy Festival five times, in 1997, 1999, 2003, 2008, and 2010.
He has been referred to as "...the funniest man in Canada. Everybody knows that," by [[Rick Mercer]] and as an emulation of "...Kramer from [[Seinfeld]]...an odd, hysterically funny, brilliant artist," by [[Mitch Fatel]].<ref>{{YouTube|-PlhvoiWd7s}}</ref>
Edwards' style is defined by his low voice and sarcastic delivery. He now lives in [[Toronto]], Ontario.
